HOME WORK: 1

1. Create a Java project, create the package and create a class with main method and print a message

2. Create a class and declare some variables of different data types such as byte, int, char, String etc....

And print the values of the declared variables

3. Play around with different data types by giving invalid data, verify the syntax errors and correct them

4. Try to execute with main method and see what happens when you don't have main method

5. Try to use the comments for the variables you declared, main method and for the class

6. Create a class and create calculator methods such as addition, subtraction...etc

Make the methods static and call them in main method